# Build Timing

- **Total build**: 100.0 ms — scan 60.0 ms + generate 40.0 ms

## Hook cost by plugin & type

Durations are measured at event emission and summed across concurrent calls, so they can exceed wall-clock on parallel builds. No-op = the hook ran but did nothing (resolveId/load/renderChunk returned nothing; transform returned the code unchanged) — a high no-op share on a hot hook means the plugin should declare a hook filter.

| Plugin | Hook | Calls | No-op | Time |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `test-plugin` | transform | 2 | 1 (50%) | 7.0 ms |
| `test-plugin` | resolveId | 2 | 1 (50%) | 3.0 ms |
| `test-plugin` | load | 1 | 1 (100%) | 1.0 ms |

